  "descriptions": [
    {
      "text": "A Famicom-only Mahjong game that teaches a specific variant called \"Attack Mahjong\" and one of many Mahjong games presented by expert Ide Yosuke. It also had its own special Mahjong controller.\n\nOne of a series of Mahjong games presented by Ide Yosuke (sort of the Dr Kawashima of early Mahjong titles), Ide Yosuke Meijin no Jissen Mahjong (or \"Ide Yosuke: Master of Attack Mahjong\") is a Mahjong game that teaches a very specific gameplay variant.\n\nIde Yosuke Meijin no Jissen Mahjong also came with its own special Mahjong controller that resembles a keyboard. The game is unplayable without it.",
      "lang": "en",
      "source": "igdb"
    }
  ]
